Package: scio
Type: Package
Title: Single-Cell Data Input/Output for R and Python
Version: 0.1.2
Authors@R: c(
    person("scio", "Contributors", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           email = "noreply@example.com")
    )
Description: Simple, efficient package for saving and loading single-cell RNA-seq
    data in a format that works seamlessly with both R (Seurat/SingleCellExperiment)
    and Python (AnnData). Preserves all data components including expression matrices,
    metadata, embeddings, and graphs.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
Depends:
    R (>= 4.0.0)
Imports:
    Matrix,
    arrow,
    digest,
    jsonlite,
    tools,
    utils
Suggests:
    reticulate,
    RcppCNPy,
    MatrixExtra,
    Seurat,
    SingleCellExperiment,
    SummarizedExperiment,
    S4Vectors,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
URL: https://github.com/bzlee-bio/scio
BugReports: https://github.com/bzlee-bio/scio/issues
